{"cross_file_issues":[],"files_reviewed":7,"findings":[],"hypotheses":[{"affected_files":["app/(ui)/pos/page.tsx"],"category":"state_lifecycle","counter_hypothesis":"","estimated_risk":"high","evidence_quote":"page.tsx:163-168: `longPressTimer.current = window.setTimeout(() => { longPressTimer.current = null; suppressProductClick.current = true; openAddQtyDialog(product) }, 500)`. page.tsx:399-402: `function handleProductClick(product: Product) { if (suppressProductClick.current) { suppressProductClick.current = false; return } ... }`. No reset on dialog close or pointerup after timeout fires.","id":"h1","state":"SUSPECTED","suspicion_reason":"When a long-press fires (`window.setTimeout` at page.tsx:163-168), `suppressProductClick.current` is set to true. The only path that clears it is in `handleProductClick` when it reads true and sets it false (line 400-402). If the user dismisses the dialog without clicking the product (e.g., taps X or Cancel), the flag remains true, causing the next legitimate click on any product to be silently consumed. This is a default-state bug: after the dialog closes, the flag should be reset to false.","title":"suppressProductClick remains true after long-press triggered dialog closes","verification_goals":["Check if suppressProductClick is reset in any handler besides handleProductClick (e.g., onPointerUp, onPointerLeave, onOpenChange callback for QtyEntryDialog).","Confirm that dialog close via onOpenChange (line 1539) does not call clearProductLongPress or reset suppressProductClick."]},{"affected_files":["components/pos/QtyEntryDialog.tsx","components/pos/CartQtyControl.tsx"],"category":"state_lifecycle","counter_hypothesis":"","estimated_risk":"medium","evidence_quote":"components/pos/QtyEntryDialog.tsx:22-24: `useEffect(() => { if (open) setDraft(String(initialQty)) }, [open, initialQty])`","id":"h2","state":"SUSPECTED","suspicion_reason":"In QtyEntryDialog, the effect `useEffect(() => { if (open) setDraft(String(initialQty)) }, [open, initialQty])` runs whenever `initialQty` changes while the dialog is open. When CartQtyControl renders QtyEntryDialog with `initialQty={qty}`, the `qty` prop can change via `onDelta` even while the dialog is open (e.g., user presses +10 preset button). This causes the draft to be overwritten with the new qty, silently discarding any digits the user has entered in the numpad. This is a stale-effect bug: the effect should only set draft when opening, not on every initialQty change.","title":"QtyEntryDialog draft is reset when initialQty changes while open","verification_goals":["Verify that QtyEntryDialog is used with initialQty={qty} in CartQtyControl (line 85): `<QtyEntryDialog initialQty={qty} ...>`.","Check if onDelta actions (e.g., +10 preset) cause qty to change while the dialog is open, triggering the effect and resetting draft.","Confirm whether initialQty should only be used as a fallback on confirm, not for reactive reset."]},{"affected_files":["app/(ui)/pos/page.tsx"],"category":"correctness","counter_hypothesis":"","estimated_risk":"medium","evidence_quote":"page.tsx:170-173: `function openAddQtyDialog(product: Product) { const stock = stockByProductId[product.id] ?? (product.initialStock ?? 0); if (stock < LOW_STOCK_THRESHOLD) { router.push('/products?restock=' + encodeURIComponent(product.id)); return } ... }`","id":"h3","state":"SUSPECTED","suspicion_reason":"In `openAddQtyDialog`, `stockByProductId[product.id] ?? (product.initialStock ?? 0)` yields 0 if both stockByProductId lookup and initialStock are undefined. Then `stock < LOW_STOCK_THRESHOLD` (0 < THRESHOLD) is likely true, causing an unexpected redirect to the restock page even for products that simply lack stock tracking data. This is a default-value bug: undefined initialStock should not be treated as zero stock.","title":"openAddQtyDialog redirects to restock when product has no stock data (undefined initialStock)","verification_goals":["Check the type of product.initialStock (likely number | undefined) and whether a missing initialStock should imply unknown stock rather than zero.","Verify LOW_STOCK_THRESHOLD value (presumably > 0, e.g., 1 or 5).","Determine if products without stock data should be allowed to add quantity via dialog instead of being redirected."]},{"affected_files":["components/pos/CartQtyControl.tsx"],"category":"state_lifecycle","counter_hypothesis":"","estimated_risk":"medium","evidence_quote":"components/pos/CartQtyControl.tsx:28 – useEffect(() => { if (!editingRef.current) setDraft(String(qty)) }, [qty])","id":"h4","state":"SUSPECTED","suspicion_reason":"The old inline cart control always displayed the exact cart quantity from state. The new CartQtyControl introduces a local `draft` state that is synced from the `qty` prop only when `editingRef.current` is false. If the parent updates `qty` (e.g., through barcode scan, bulk delta, or other cart modifications) while the user is editing the draft input, the draft will not reflect the new external value, leading to a stale displayed quantity. The `useEffect` at line 28 guards with `if (!editingRef.current) setDraft(String(qty))`, so during editing the draft is frozen. The user may commit based on an outdated base value.","title":"CartQtyControl local draft may become stale when cart quantity is updated externally during editing","verification_goals":["Check if any caller updates the `qty` prop of CartQtyControl while the component is mounted (e.g., page.tsx setQty triggered by barcode scanner or other delta)","Simulate scenario: user edits input, external setQty fires (e.g., via barcode), then user blurs – verify that commitDraft uses the stale `qty` fallback from closed-over value or the updated prop? (commitDraft calls commitCartQty(raw, qty) where `qty` is the prop at render time, not the external update).","Confirm if external updates to cart qty are possible while CartQtyControl input is focused (e.g., via keyboard shortcuts or other tabs)."]},{"affected_files":["lib/cart-qty.ts"],"category":"validation","counter_hypothesis":"","estimated_risk":"medium","evidence_quote":"lib/cart-qty.ts:7 – `const n = Number(trimmed)`","id":"h11","state":"SUSPECTED","suspicion_reason":"When a user types a hex string like '0x10' into the non-touch input (CartQtyControl) and blurs, `Number('0x10')` evaluates to 16. `parseCartQty` only checks `isFinite` and `n < 0`, so it returns 16. The intended behavior is to accept only decimal integer strings (as the QtyNumpad enforces), but the backend parser silently accepts hex notation, allowing unintended quantity values (e.g., '0xFF' → 255).","title":"parseCartQty accepts hex-formatted input strings, bypassing intended digit-only validation","verification_goals":["Test parseCartQty with inputs '0x10', '0xFF', '0x0' to confirm they return non-null values","Check if any input sanitization exists in CartQtyControl's onBlur path before calling commitCartQty","Determine whether hex acceptance is intentional or an oversight given QtyNumpad's digit-only constraint"]},{"affected_files":["components/pos/QtyEntryDialog.tsx"],"category":"state_lifecycle","counter_hypothesis":"","estimated_risk":"low","evidence_quote":"components/pos/QtyEntryDialog.tsx:30 – useEffect(() => { if (open) setDraft(String(initialQty)) }, [open, initialQty])","id":"h5","state":"SUSPECTED","suspicion_reason":"The `QtyEntryDialog` resets its `draft` state to `String(initialQty)` when `open` becomes true (via useEffect). However, if `initialQty` changes while the dialog is already open (e.g., the product switches due to a rapid interaction), the draft will not be updated until the dialog closes and reopens. This could cause the user to confirm a quantity based on the old product's `initialQty`.","title":"QtyEntryDialog draft resets on open but does not handle stale initialQty when dialog is already open","verification_goals":["Check if `initialQty` prop can change while `open` is true (e.g., caller `page.tsx` sets `addQtyProduct` to a new product before closing the dialog)","Verify that the useEffect dependency includes `initialQty` – it does, so it should reset when `initialQty` changes even if `open` remains true. But the condition `if (open)` may be true; the effect runs and resets draft. However, the reset happens after render; if the user has typed, that edit is overwritten. This could be intentional but may be surprising."]},{"affected_files":["components/pos/CartQtyControl.tsx","components/pos/QtyEntryDialog.tsx"],"category":"correctness","counter_hypothesis":"","estimated_risk":"low","evidence_quote":"CartQtyControl.tsx:65-68: `toast.warning(\"Only ${stockAvailable.toLocaleString()} ${stockUnit ?? 'in stock'}\", { description: 'Quantity updated — adjust if needed.' })`; QtyEntryDialog.tsx:53-56: `toast.warning(\"Only ${stockAvailable.toLocaleString()} ${stockUnit ?? 'in stock'}\", { description: 'Quantity saved — adjust if needed.' })`","id":"h9","state":"SUSPECTED","suspicion_reason":"Both `CartQtyControl.tsx` and `QtyEntryDialog.tsx` show a `toast.warning` when the entered quantity exceeds `stockAvailable`. The descriptions differ: 'Quantity updated — adjust if needed.' vs 'Quantity saved — adjust if needed.'. This inconsistency in user-facing messaging may confuse users as to whether the quantity was actually committed, and indicates a DRY violation where the shared warning string was not extracted into a single source.","title":"Stock warning toast messages differ between CartQtyControl and QtyEntryDialog","verification_goals":["compare the exact toast.warning calls in CartQtyControl.tsx and QtyEntryDialog.tsx","determine if the difference is intentional (e.g., one context is 'updating' the other is 'saving') or accidental"]}],"scope":"scope: staged (index vs HEAD)","summary":"Reviewed 7 files: 1 confirmed, 2 disproven, 1 advisory, 6 suspected-unverified (6 grounding_rejected) — see unverified_hypotheses. Three edge/default-state hypotheses found: (1) suppressProductClick not reset after long-press dialog close, causing next click to be eaten; (2) QtyEntryDialog draft resets when initialQty changes while dialog is open; (3) openAddQtyDialog redirects to restock when product lacks stock data, treating undefined as zero. | Four hypotheses identified: draft staleness in CartQtyControl and QtyEntryDialog, missing stock check in addToCart path from confirmAddQty, and potential dangling reference to removed import. The draft staleness issues are new state-lifecycle risks introduced by the refactor; the stock-check gap weakens the pre-existing guard; the import removal is low risk but warrants verification. | The diff introduces a new quantity-entry subsystem with reusable components and a utility library. Cross-file contracts are mostly consistent, but there is a high-risk hypothesis about a potentially missing import for `LOW_STOCK_THRESHOLD` in the main page. Additionally, two duplicated stock warning messages differ slightly, and a long-press timeout lacks lifecycle cleanup. These should be verified to ensure correctness and maintainability. | One suspected parsing/format robustness issue: `parseCartQty` uses `Number()` which accepts hex notation, bypassing the digit-only expectation set by the QtyNumpad UX. No other confirmed parsing bugs identified. | Two state-mutation invariant hypotheses identified: (1) a global suppressProductClick flag is not cleared on new product interactions, leading to suppressed clicks after a long press; (2) the product reference used by confirmAddQty can become stale if the dialog is still open when a new long press occurs, risking addition of the wrong product.","unverified_hypotheses":[{"affected_files":["app/(ui)/pos/page.tsx"],"category":"state_lifecycle","estimated_risk":"high","id":"h12","reason":"grounding_rejected","title":"Global suppressProductClick flag not cleared on new pointer-down, causing subsequent clicks to be erroneously suppressed"},{"affected_files":["app/(ui)/pos/page.tsx"],"category":"correctness","estimated_risk":"high","id":"h8","reason":"grounding_rejected","title":"Missing import for LOW_STOCK_THRESHOLD in pos/page.tsx"},{"affected_files":["app/(ui)/pos/page.tsx"],"category":"state_lifecycle","estimated_risk":"medium","id":"h10","reason":"grounding_rejected","title":"Long-press timeout not cleaned up on component unmount in pos/page.tsx"},{"affected_files":["app/(ui)/pos/page.tsx"],"category":"state_lifecycle","estimated_risk":"medium","id":"h13","reason":"grounding_rejected","title":"Stale product reference in confirmAddQty if addQtyProduct changes while dialog is open"},{"affected_files":["app/(ui)/pos/page.tsx"],"category":"validation","estimated_risk":"medium","id":"h6","reason":"grounding_rejected","title":"Old stock-check guard not propagated to `addToCart` from `confirmAddQty`"},{"affected_files":["app/(ui)/pos/page.tsx"],"category":"correctness","estimated_risk":"low","id":"h7","reason":"grounding_rejected","title":"Removed `posQtyBtnClass` import but class used in same file? No, moved to CartQtyControl, but no import left in page.tsx – could cause runtime error if accidentally referenced elsewhere in page.tsx"}],"verdict":"NEEDS_FIX","verified_correct":[{"description":"New lib/cart-qty.ts exports are consistently imported and used across CartQtyControl and QtyEntryDialog (commitCartQty, QTY_STEP_PRESETS).","files":["lib/cart-qty.ts","components/pos/CartQtyControl.tsx","components/pos/QtyEntryDialog.tsx"]},{"description":"CartQtyControl and QtyEntryDialog correctly receive and forward deviceUiMode, stockAvailable, and stockUnit props, matching the prop interfaces.","files":["components/pos/CartQtyControl.tsx","components/pos/QtyEntryDialog.tsx","app/(ui)/pos/page.tsx"]}],"verified_findings":[{"computed_confidence":0,"counter_evidence":[{"depth":"shallow","description":"The useEffect at line 45–47 of QtyEntryDialog.tsx includes `initialQty` in its dependency array. When `open` is true and `initialQty` changes, the effect executes `setDraft(String(initialQty))`, resetting the draft to the new value. Therefore a stale old-product quantity cannot persist.","file_path":"components/pos/QtyEntryDialog.tsx","line_number":45,"reliability":0.98,"type":"symbol_resolution"}],"fix_hint":"","hypothesis_id":"h5","severity":"low","supporting_evidence":[],"verdict":"DISPROVEN","verification_trace":[{"justification":"Read the suspect file to understand the useEffect and its dependencies, verifying whether initialQty change while open triggers a draft reset.","outcome":"[Lines 1-100 of 117]
'use client'

import { useEffect, useState } from 'react'
import * as Dialog from '@radix-ui/react-dialog'
import { X } from 'lucide-react'
import { toast } from 'sonner'
import { commitCartQty } from '@/lib/cart-qty'
import { posActionBtnClass, posDialogContentClass, type DeviceUiMode } from '@/lib/device-ui'
import { QtyNumpad } from '@/components/pos/QtyNumpad'

type QtyEntryDialogProps = {
  open: boolean
  onOpenChange: (open: boolean) => void
  title: string
  subtitle?: string
  initialQty: number
  onConfirm: (qty: number) => void
  deviceUiMode: DeviceUiMode
  stockAvailable?: number | null
  stockUnit?: string
  confirmLabel?: string
  allowZero?: boolean
}

export function QtyEntryDialog({
  open,
  onOpenChange,
  title,
  subtitle,
  initialQty,
  onConfirm,
  deviceUiMode,
  stockAvailable,
  stockUnit,
  confirmLabel = 'OK',
  allowZero = false,
}: QtyEntryDialogProps) {
  const [draft, setDraft] = useState(String(initialQty))

  useEffect(() => {
    if (open) setDraft(String(initialQty))
  }, [open, initialQty])

  function handleConfirm() {
    const qty = commitCartQty(draft, initialQty)
    if (qty <= 0 && !allowZero) {
      toast.error('Enter a quantity of at least 1')
      return
    }
    if (stockAvailable != null && qty > stockAvailable) {
      toast.warning(`Only ${stockAvailable.toLocaleString()} ${stockUnit ?? 'in stock'}`, {
        description: 'Quantity saved — adjust if needed.',
      })
    }
    onConfirm(qty)
    onOpenChange(false)
  }

  const stockHint =
    stockAvailable != null
      ? `${stockAvailable.toLocaleString()} ${stockUnit ?? 'available'}`
      : null

  return (
    <Dialog.Root open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
      <Dialog.Portal>
        <Dialog.Overlay className="fixed inset-0 bg-black/40 backdrop-blur-sm z-[60]" />
        <Dialog.Content className={`${posDialogContentClass(deviceUiMode)} z-[60]`}>
          <div className="flex items-start justify-between gap-3 mb-4 shrink-0">
            <div className="min-w-0">
              <Dialog.Title className="text-lg font-semibold">{title}</Dialog.Title>
              {subtitle && <p className="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-0.5 truncate">{subtitle}</p>}
            </div>
            <Dialog.Close asChild>
              <button
                type="button"
                className="shrink-0 text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-600 p-1 rounded-md"
                aria-label="Close"
              >
                <X size={18} />
              </button>
            </Dialog.Close>
          </div>

          <div className="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 px-4 py-3 mb-4">
            <p className="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Quantity</p>
            <p className="text-3xl font-semibold tabular-nums text-gray-900 min-h-10">
              {draft || '0'}
            </p>
            {stockHint && <p className="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">In stock: {stockHint}</p>}
          </div>

          <QtyNumpad value={draft} onChange={setDraft} deviceUiMode={deviceUiMode} />

          <div className="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 mt-5 shrink-0">
            <Dialog.Close asChild>
              <button
                type="button"
                className={`border border-gray-300 rounded-xl font-medium text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 ${posActionBtnClass(deviceUiMode)} py-2.5`}
              >
